// ====================================================
// NOTES ON POSITION CALCULATION
// ====================================================
// When using mixed scaling (e.g., one 4K scaled, one 1080p native):
// 1. The 4K TV with scale 1.5 has LOGICAL size 2560x1440
// 2. The 1080p monitor has LOGICAL size 1920x1080
// 3. To place them side by side, the right monitor starts at x = (left monitor's LOGICAL width)
// 4. Example: position x=2560 y=0 (not x=3840!)
//
// Run `niri msg outputs` to see your current logical positions
